Parliament, Monday 29 July 2019 – The National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will at its plenary sitting tomorrow, consider the 2019 Appropriation Bill.
	
	The Bill adopted by the National Assembly (NA) last week, will now be processed by the NCOP for concurrence - as required by Section 213 of the Constitution and Section 26 of the Public Finance Management Act (PFMA). The PFMA requires that Parliament’s two houses, the NA and the NCOP, authorize the allocation of money from the National Revenue Fund to various state institutions to enable its expenditure.
	
	DETAILS OF THE NCOP SITTING ARE AS FOLLOWS:
	Date: Tuesday, 30 July 2019
	Time: 11.00
	Venue: NCOP Chamber, Parliament
	
	Media wishing to photograph the NCOP Sitting or to receive a feed from Parliament should send their details to the officials listed below. Media who do not have parliamentary media access permits and who wish to attend the sittings should also notify the officials listed below.
	
	Details needed are: full name, ID or passport number, name of media organization, designation (eg. photographer, writer) and contact details.
	
	Mlindi Mpindi: mmpindi@parliament.gov.za (081 716 7329 or 021 403 2340)
	Masego Dlula: mdlula@parliament.gov.za (081 715 9398 or 021 403 8141)
	
